Energy utilization is another aspect to be considered in the system design. In the SEn-BS system, a capacity mismatch between PV panels and the battery bank (e.g., oversized PV panels or undersized battery bank) could potentially cause solar energy loss. Conversely, the reasonable capacity match between them could improve solar energy utilization and avoid blind capital spending. Thus, the SEuE, denoted as γseue, is defined as the rate of the total amount of energy units stored in the battery bank and consumed by the BS to the total amount of harvested energy units. It can be derived as: 
(23)γseue=λe1−p̂EBmaxλe=1p0+ρ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
